%N A396261 Decimal expansion of the smallest positive root to 64*x^6 - 672*x^4 + 1764*x^2 - 1323 = 0.
%C A396261 Negated imaginary part of the Gauss sum tau(chi^2) = Sum_{a=0..6} chi(a)^2*exp(2*Pi*i/7), where chi is the Dirichlet character modulo 7 such that chi(3) = exp(2*Pi*i/6). Note that tau(chi^2) is a root to x^6 - 7*x^3 + 343 = 0.
%H A396261 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A396261/b396261.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
